            <scopecontent id="aspace_dae9c005f64e78fc283d02e1434a32f5">
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
               <p>The series is arranged alphabetically by material type. It is comprised of materials relating to both the Kameelfontein and Vergelegen estates that document their purchase, management and eventual sale. Also included are descriptions of the physical geography of the two estates. Materials in the General folder are arranged chronologically, and include power of attorney documents, miscellaneous letters, land survey papers, inspection reports, and newspaper clippings. Correspondence is divided into two subgroups, Alphabetical and Topical. Alphabetical correspondence is comprised of outgoing letters arranged by the sender's last name. Topical correspondence is arranged alphabetically by subject matter, and contain numerous letters which document specific events and transactions that occurred in relation to the properties. In addition, there is a small collection of maps and plans, copies of the contemporary newspaper, <title render="italic">
                     <part>Staats-Courant</part>
                  </title>, two original photographs of the Pilgrim's Rest goldfields, and several original and translated title deeds.</p>
            </scopecontent>
